# Encryption and Key Management

## Field-level encryption

- Implemented via prisma-field-encryption; see app/prisma/schema.prisma for /// @encrypted annotations
- Encrypted fields include PII/secrets like User.email, AccountRegister.name, RegisterEntry.description, plaid secrets, wallet addresses, and Reoccurrence.description
- generator fieldEncryptionMigrations writes app/prisma/reencrypt/* with migrate helpers

## Re-encryption and local restore

- docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md documents dev restore behavior
  - scripts/dump-and-restore.sh calls scripts/reset-encrypted-users-after-restore.ts
  - Plan describes auto-generated re-encrypt path using prisma/reencrypt + placeholder fallback for missing source keys
- app/prisma/reencrypt/* and microservice/prisma/reencrypt/* are generated; do not modify by hand

## Key rotation (staging)

- .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml runs nightly CronJob using the microservice runner-keyrotate image
- .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml grants Role/RoleBinding to patch the SECRET_DB and roll Deployments in namespace
- Microservice exposes routes/migrate.* to run migrations post-rotation

## Services

- app/server/services/RsaService.ts and JwtService.ts provide asymmetric and JWT operations
- app/server/lib/rotateUserJwtKey.ts supports per-user JWT key rotation

## Environment variables

- DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY and optional DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_* are read from secrets in Kubernetes
- Never commit secrets; pre-commit hooks and TruffleHog detectors enforce hygiene (.trufflehog-detectors.yaml)

